net.markenwerk.commons.datastructures

Interface OptionalSelection<Payload,Result>

  • Type Parameters:
    Payload - The payload type.
    Result - The result type.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractConvertingOptionalSelection, AbstractOptionalSelection, ConvertingOptionalSelection, NullOptionalSelection

    public interface OptionalSelection<Payload,Result>
    An OptionalSelection can be used to handle an Optional and obtain a result value, whether the Optional has a value or not.
    Since:
    1.3.0
    Author:
    Torsten Krause (tk at markenwerk dot net)

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Result onNoValue()
      Called by the handled Optional if it has no payload value.
      Result onValue(Payload payload)
      Called by the handled Optional if it has has a value.
